{
  "article_id": "SacramentoDailyRecordUnion1881",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "More fine marble has been found in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Utah",
        "entity_key": "st_utah",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A steam flour mill is talked of in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Fall Brook",
        "entity_key": "ci_fabr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego county",
        "entity_key": "co_sdcounty",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Squirrel poison killed a number of horses for "
      },
      {
        "text": "a Stanislaus farmer",
        "entity_key": "stanfarm",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "the other day."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Some Vallejo gentlemen",
        "entity_key": "valmen",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "are about to send "
      },
      {
        "text": "a man",
        "entity_key": "man25",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Alaska",
        "entity_key": "st_ak",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to locate mines. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Grant county, New Mexico",
        "entity_key": "co_grant",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", offers $100 per head for scalps of hostile "
      },
      {
        "text": "Apaches",
        "entity_key": "natam_apache",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The Calistogian",
        "entity_key": "calist",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "figures the wine product of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Napa county",
        "entity_key": "co_napa",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to be 2,910,750 gallons."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "There are at present twenty-two buildings in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Astoria, Or.",
        "entity_key": "ci_astoria",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in course of erection."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A large number of beaver and other fur-bearing animals have recently been trapped in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Jackson county, Oregon",
        "entity_key": "co_jackson",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The staff of surveyors from "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Bernardino",
        "entity_key": "co_sbern",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "on the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Southern California Railroad",
        "entity_key": "socalrail",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "are in the canyon, heading toward "
      },
      {
        "text": "Temecula",
        "entity_key": "ci_tem",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Forty-seven men and women, new arrivals from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Switzerland",
        "entity_key": "co_sz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", came to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Sonoma valley",
        "entity_key": "re_son",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "last Wednesday to permanently locate there."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Stone coal is now the main excitement in the region of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ten-Mile and Looking-Glass, Douglas county, Oregon",
        "entity_key": "re_tmgl",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The impression is that the coal exists under most of the hills of that region."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Near "
      },
      {
        "text": "Canyonville, Douglas county, Or.",
        "entity_key": "ci_canville",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "a 12-year-old boy",
        "entity_key": "boy5",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was hunting and met two panthers. He wounded one, and was attacked by the animal. Help arrived and both panthers were killed."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "After the late flood, farmers along "
      },
      {
        "text": "Bear creek, Jackson county, Oregon",
        "entity_key": "re_bearcreek",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", were busy gathering up rails that had lodged in the willows. The rule is that all rails that are washed on a man's land are considered to be his property."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The annual report of "
      },
      {
        "text": "P. Evarts",
        "entity_key": "evarts",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the Superintendent of the Eureka and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Palisade Railroad",
        "entity_key": "palrail",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", shows that during the year 1880 the net profit was $248,232 94. The same official reports of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ruby Hill Railroad",
        "entity_key": "rhrail",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "that its net profit was $80,741 18."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The work of preparing the old broom factory at "
      },
      {
        "text": "South Vallejo",
        "entity_key": "re_soval",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for a fish cannery is progressing. About $30,000 will be represented in the enterprise. About seventy hands will be employed, and the canning capacity will be 200 cases daily. Canning will begin in about a month."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Hancock",
        "entity_key": "ci_han",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is the name bestowed on the new town in the copper district in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mason Valley, Esmeralda county, Nev",
        "entity_key": "re_mason",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The name was given last fall during the campaign, when it was said it could produce more fights to the quart of whisky than any town of its size in "
      },
      {
        "text": "the State",
        "entity_key": "st_nv",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In the Art Loan Exhibition at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "there is a bone needle, a memento of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who was rescued by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". When the tribe was removed to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", by accident "
      },
      {
        "text": "this woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was left behind, and for a long term of years she lived alone on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "At "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Fe, New Mexico",
        "entity_key": "ci_sanfe",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the other day, a new railroad company known as the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Jemez Valley Hot Springs Railroad Company",
        "entity_key": "jvhsrail",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", was organized. This is the first company of the kind ever organized by citizens of the Territory. The road will run from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Bernalillo",
        "entity_key": "ci_berna",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to the famous "
      },
      {
        "text": "Jemez Hot Springs",
        "entity_key": "re_jemezsprings",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a distance of about thirty miles."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A number of citizens of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Leadville, Co.",
        "entity_key": "ci_lead",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", have asked that the saloons, gaming houses, theaters and bagnios be closed on Sunday. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The City Attorney",
        "entity_key": "attorney",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was instructed to draw up an ordinance to that effect, including also the business houses. The "
      },
      {
        "text": "Merchants' Protective Association",
        "entity_key": "merchasc",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "have called a meeting to protest."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "At "
      },
      {
        "text": "Clark Ranch",
        "entity_key": "clarkranch",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", near "
      },
      {
        "text": "Leadville, Col.",
        "entity_key": "ci_lead",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a miner named "
      },
      {
        "text": "Gavin",
        "entity_key": "miner",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was recently, while in his cabin, buried under a snow-slide. The fire was out, and soon he was in darkness. He must escape, so he began to dig a tunnel. He worked till his hands were benumbed and frozen. He worked thus for six days and escaped, but is not expected to live."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The principal losses of cattle in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Wyoming",
        "entity_key": "st_wy",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Colorado",
        "entity_key": "st_co",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nebraska",
        "entity_key": "st_neb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "have been on the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Laramie plains",
        "entity_key": "re_laramie",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and along the line of the railroad toward the east and on the south, and the severest have been on the ranges between the "
      },
      {
        "text": "North",
        "entity_key": "re_nplatte",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "South Platte rivers",
        "entity_key": "re_splate",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", east of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Julesburg",
        "entity_key": "ci_jules",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". In the sections mentioned 10 to 15 per cent. of the cattle have died, and in some "
      },
      {
        "text": "Colorado",
        "entity_key": "st_co",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "herds the loss has gone as high as 50 per cent."
      }
    ]
  ]
}